    <bioghist>
      <head>Historical note</head>
      <p>The Summer Hill Congregational Church was founded on April 17, 1827, with seventy members
        and had begun earlier that year as The East Church of Locke and the East Congregational
        Society of Locke. Fire claimed the original church building in January of 1841 but the
        church quickly built a new building and dedicated it in September of that year. That new
        building served the church on the Homer-Locke Highway, Route 90, for the remainder of its
        history. The church was rededicated in May 1896. The church is also known as the one-word
        variant "Summerhill," as is the town it served.</p>
      <p>The church was part of a local consortium of churches known as the Cortland Larger Parish,
        formed in 1925, that also included the Second Congregational Church of Cortland and the
        Congregational Church of Groton. The Cortland Larger Parish dissolved with the exit of the
        Cortland church in 1947 and was replaced by an entity known as the Tri-County Parish,
        comprising churches in the counties of Cortland, Cayuga, and Tompkins. The church's final
        affiliation was part of the Cortland-Summer Hill Parish.</p>
      <p>Members of a single family served as clerk for Summer Hill Congregational Church for more
        than a century, 1835 to 1838. The legacy began with Winslow Hamblin, who was followed by his
        son-in-law, George Allen, who was in turn followed by his son, J. Gurnsey Allen, who held
        the post for 41 years.</p>
      <p>Members of the church voted to close the church permanently and sell its assets on May 5,
        1974. The church held its last service on September 29, 1974.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent>
      <head>Scope and Contents</head>
      <p>This collection contains administrative records of the Summer Hill, N.Y., Congregational
        Church and records of the Cortland-Summer Hill Parish, of which the church was a member.</p>
    </scopecontent>
    <arrangement>
      <head>Arrangement</head>
      <p>The collection is arranged into two series. Records in each series have been arranged
        chronologically by start date.</p>
      <p><emph render="bold">Series 1:</emph> Summer Hill Congregational Church records,
        1831-1977</p>
      <p><emph render="bold">Series 2:</emph> Cortland-Summer Hill Parish records, 1940-1955</p>
    </arrangement>
    <relatedmaterial>
      <head>Related Materials</head>
      <p>Additional materials related to the Summer Hill Congregational Church, N.Y. are located at
        the Cornell University Library's Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, #6275.</p>
    </relatedmaterial>
